            },
            "description": "Together with our M&A International partner office in New York, TM Capital, we approached more than 150 international strategic and financial players, creating a competitive process. As a result our client, Proliance International Inc. (AMEX: PLI), successfully sold 100% of the shares in Nederlandse Radiateuren Fabriek B.V. (NRF), an aftermarket and OEM manufacturer and distributor of a complete range of heat-transfer products, to Banco Products Ltd., an Indian, publicly listed manufacturer and supplier of engine cooling components and engine sealing gaskets to the global commercial and industrial automotive market.\n\nThe transaction was completed pursuant to Section 363 of the U.S. bankruptcy code. A \u2018stalking horse\u2019 agreement, which Proliance entered into, produced competitive bids from two strategic buyers from India and China. Both Asian parties were very interested to obtain control over NRF\u2019s broad European distribution and state-of-the-art manufacturing facilities. During the final sale auction held in New York both parties contended heavily in this last and crucial phase. Banco Products won this auction and successfully acquired NRF for EUR 17.7 million.\n",
